We did our best to support the old 1.0 wad files in HHexen 1.5, but we strongly
suggest that you always patch your wads to version 1.1 to avoid possible issues.
If, for some reason, patching is not an option and you run into problems, then
compile hhexen to specifically use version 1.0 hexen.wad:
  ./configure --enable-oldwad

Remember that saved games and recorded demos from different wad versions are not
compatible.

If you don't have the full retail version of Hexen, you can still play the demo
version.  We suggest that you download the demo wad from our site:  it is the
the 4-level version 1.1 demo wad file from the MacHexen shareware.  On the other
hand, the PC shareware wad is a version 1.0 wad and we don't recommend it. (If
you specifically want to use the PC demo and ordinary hhexen gives you trouble
with it, recompiling hhexen with the --enable-oldwad configuration might help.)

